<TITLE> Hamid claims fair play </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 New York, Apr 20 (bdnews24.com)  The opposition is given the floor for longer than it deserves in the parliament, claimed the speaker on Tuesday. Speaking at reception given by expatriates in New York, Abdul Hamid, speaker of the ninth parliament, said that he gave the floor to the opposition for longer than was called for. Hamid said that he did it deliberately to strengthen democracy. Parliament of the national speaker Abdul Hamid on Tuesday said that Bangladesh had made great strides on the way to democracy. Hamid told the reception that despite all the obstacles, Bangladesh had already improved substantially, as far as democracy was concerned, especially compared to many other countries. Hamid reached New York on Apr 18 for attending a UN plenary session of parliament speakers across the world. A high ranking diplomat of the Bangladesh embassy told bdnews24.com that Hamid would leave New York for Washington DC later in the day. Hamid is scheduled for a personal meeting with Nancy Pelosi, speaker of the US Congress. bdne
